\fBNOTE: \fRFrom OTP R16 the \fInumeric version\fR represents the version of the OpenSSL \fIheader files\fR (\fIopenssl/opensslv.h\fR) used when crypto was compiled. The text variant represents the libcrypto library used at runtime. In earlier OTP versions both numeric and text was taken from the library.



