.br
.RS
.PP
Generate a random integer in a specified range.

.PP
The returned random integer is in the interval is \fI0\fR =< \fIN\fR < \fIRange\fR.

.PP
Uses the \fIcrypto\fR library random number generator \fIBN_rand_range\fR.

.PP
If the \fIRange\fR argument is a \fIpos_integer/0\fR the return value is a \fInon_neg_integer/0\fR.  If the \fIRange\fR argument is a positive integer in a \fIbinary/0\fR, the return value is a non-negative integer in a \fIbinary/0\fR.

.PP
May raise exception \fIerror:low_entropy\fR in case the random generator failed due to lack of secure "randomness".


